I called it a what?
A secret song?

00:15:49.116 --> 00:15:52.186 position:38% line:83% align:start
You sang it so much,
it got stuck in my head.

00:15:52.219 --> 00:15:54.054 position:52% line:83% align:start
How can you
 <i>not</i> remember it?

00:15:54.087 --> 00:15:57.525 position:5% line:83% align:start
I remember the melody,
but that's all.

00:15:57.559 --> 00:16:01.261 position:30% line:83% align:start
That makes sense, since
the lyrics are gibberish.

00:16:01.295 --> 00:16:05.733 position:7% line:83% align:start
[ Gasps ] Yukimaru!
Do you remember <i>all</i> the lyrics?

00:16:05.767 --> 00:16:08.202 position:55% line:5% align:start
Unh. Yes.

00:16:08.235 --> 00:16:10.437 position:41% line:5% align:start
"More than golden,
the land of the gods.

00:16:10.471 --> 00:16:13.407 position:30% line:5% align:start
Atop the lattice stage,
dance, oh, shrine maiden.

00:16:13.440 --> 00:16:15.976 position:35% line:5% align:start
Far across the waves,
the maid slumbers.

00:16:16.009 --> 00:16:17.946 position:44% line:5% align:start
What came before
southern snows,

00:16:17.978 --> 00:16:19.848 position:55% line:5% align:start
the hour
of the cold flames.

00:16:19.881 --> 00:16:21.281 position:19% line:5% align:start
Waters of the darkest blue.

00:16:21.315 --> 00:16:23.350 position:41% line:5% align:start
White storm clouds,
they call your name.

00:16:23.383 --> 00:16:25.052 position:52% line:5% align:start
Here it is,
the journey's end,

00:16:25.085 --> 00:16:26.588 position:55% line:5% align:start
the stone
that shows the way.

00:16:26.621 --> 00:16:29.156 position:21% line:5% align:start
What lies ahead is the sun
setting in the east.

00:16:29.189 --> 00:16:32.392 position:30% line:5% align:start
Now is the time to run,
where the ark will lead us."

00:16:32.426 --> 00:16:35.395 position:47% line:83% align:start
"Where the ark.
will lead us."

00:16:35.429 --> 00:16:37.832 position:52% line:83% align:start
"Waters of
the darkest blue."

00:16:37.866 --> 00:16:40.400 position:35% line:89% align:start
"White storm clouds."

00:16:40.434 --> 00:16:41.401 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:16:41.435 --> 00:16:43.337 position:41% line:83% align:start
Voice:
Which wilt thou choose?

00:16:43.370 --> 00:16:47.942 position:35% line:83% align:start
Blue water?
Or storm clouds?

00:16:47.976 --> 00:16:50.845 position:44% line:83% align:start
Fena: Blue water
or storm clouds.

00:16:50.879 --> 00:16:53.013 position:41% line:89% align:start
The maid slumbers.

00:16:53.046 --> 00:16:55.315 position:55% line:83% align:start
The stone
that shows the way.

00:16:55.349 --> 00:16:58.085 position:55% line:83% align:start
The hour
of the cold flames.

00:16:58.118 --> 00:17:00.889 position:21% line:83% align:start
They match what we've seen
and done so far.

00:17:00.922 --> 00:17:01.956 position:16% line:83% align:start
Fena.
[ Gasps ]

00:17:01.990 --> 00:17:03.457 position:50% line:83% align:start
Do you think
that maybe that song

00:17:03.490 --> 00:17:06.861 position:44% line:83% align:start
might be pointing
to Eden's destination?

00:17:06.895 --> 00:17:08.930 position:38% line:83% align:start
When I first arrived
at the island,

00:17:08.963 --> 00:17:10.665 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yukihisa did say something.

00:17:10.698 --> 00:17:13.902 position:10% line:83% align:start
Surely your father must have
told you about this item

00:17:13.935 --> 00:17:16.838 position:19% line:89% align:start
in some way or another.

00:17:16.871 --> 00:17:18.038 position:61% line:89% align:start
Remember?

00:17:18.071 --> 00:17:21.108 position:38% line:83% align:start
O'Malley needed both
the location <i>and</i> me.

00:17:21.141 --> 00:17:23.143 position:24% line:83% align:start
Because apparently,
we will need both the girl

00:17:23.176 --> 00:17:25.547 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>and</i> the coordinates.

00:17:25.580 --> 00:17:28.115 position:38% line:83% align:start
If these lyrics were
taught only to me,

00:17:28.148 --> 00:17:32.286 position:16% line:83% align:start
it might be because it hints
at the location of Eden!

00:17:32.319 --> 00:17:36.056 position:5% line:83% align:start
"Atop the lattice stage,
dance, oh, shrine maiden"?

00:17:36.089 --> 00:17:40.093 position:33% line:83% align:start
Well, maybe we haven't
gotten to that part.

00:17:40.127 --> 00:17:43.463 position:5% line:83% align:start
Fena, do you remember
the pedestal?

00:17:43.497 --> 00:17:45.299 position:52% line:89% align:start
Huh? Yeah.

00:17:45.332 --> 00:17:47.334 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'd wager Karin's theory
was correct,

00:17:47.367 --> 00:17:49.704 position:5% line:83% align:start
and it was almost certainly
the face of a clock.

00:17:49.737 --> 00:17:50.738 position:58% line:89% align:start
Right!

00:17:50.772 --> 00:17:54.274 position:7% line:83% align:start
You can use a clock
to tell time and direction.

00:17:54.308 --> 00:17:57.344 position:5% line:83% align:start
The stone only had time
etched into it.

00:17:57.377 --> 00:17:59.547 position:10% line:83% align:start
Why was direction
left out?

00:17:59.581 --> 00:18:02.050 position:7% line:5% align:start
Are we supposed to
pair up that time

00:18:02.082 --> 00:18:03.183 position:10% line:5% align:start
to the directions
in the lyrics?

00:18:03.216 --> 00:18:06.486 position:35% line:5% align:start
If so, that leaves us
two numbers.

00:18:06.521 --> 00:18:10.658 position:33% line:5% align:start
There's "61" and "34,"
written in Roman numerals.

00:18:10.692 --> 00:18:15.095 position:7% line:5% align:start
"What came before."
"What lies ahead."

00:18:15.128 --> 00:18:17.966 position:10% line:5% align:start
The sands of time
flow from top to bottom.

00:18:17.999 --> 00:18:19.534 position:10% line:5% align:start
In other words...

00:18:19.567 --> 00:18:23.871 position:41% line:5% align:start
61 degrees is south
and 34 is east?

00:18:23.905 --> 00:18:25.172 position:19% line:5% align:start
That's what
it must mean.

00:18:25.205 --> 00:18:27.374 position:69% line:5% align:start
Hmm.
What's wrong?

00:18:27.407 --> 00:18:31.746 position:13% line:5% align:start
Something about it seems off,
but I can't explain why.

00:18:31.779 --> 00:18:36.116 position:27% line:83% align:start
Also, the order of where
we visited is reversed.

00:18:37.585 --> 00:18:39.453 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:18:45.994 --> 00:18:47.729 position:52% line:89% align:start
What, Fena?

00:18:47.762 --> 00:18:50.297 position:41% line:89% align:start
I just remembered.

00:18:50.330 --> 00:18:51.131 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:18:51.164 --> 00:18:53.034 position:5% line:89% align:start
I remembered something!

00:18:53.067 --> 00:18:54.068 position:52% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:18:54.102 --> 00:18:56.104 position:16% line:83% align:start
What the song
was called!

00:18:56.136 --> 00:18:57.538 position:5% line:89% align:start
It was "Vice Versa"!

00:18:57.572 --> 00:18:59.641 position:16% line:89% align:start
"Vice Versa."

00:18:59.674 --> 00:19:03.911 position:5% line:83% align:start
"The reverse also holds true"
in Latin.

00:19:03.945 --> 00:19:06.080 position:16% line:89% align:start
The reverse.

00:19:06.114 --> 00:19:08.116 position:7% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ] I get it!

00:19:08.148 --> 00:19:11.019 position:19% line:83% align:start
The answer
isn't south and east!

00:19:11.052 --> 00:19:12.285 position:61% line:5% align:start
Fena:
It's north and west!

00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:14.388 position:13% line:5% align:start
Past and future
are also reversed --

00:19:14.421 --> 00:19:17.157 position:13% line:5% align:start
in other words,
flipped vertically.

00:19:17.190 --> 00:19:21.461 position:5% line:83% align:start
61 degrees west longitude.
34 degrees north latitude.

00:19:21.495 --> 00:19:24.866 position:24% line:83% align:start
Then, I think the numbers
are reversed, too!

00:19:24.899 --> 00:19:28.235 position:41% line:5% align:start
That would explain
why they're in Roman numerals

00:19:28.268 --> 00:19:30.772 position:52% line:5% align:start
instead of
standard Arabic!

00:19:33.041 --> 00:19:34.976 position:27% line:89% align:start
So...

00:19:35.009 --> 00:19:37.078 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's 14 degrees west...

00:19:37.111 --> 00:19:39.080 position:5% line:89% align:start
and 63 degrees north.

00:19:39.113 --> 00:19:43.283 position:38% line:83% align:start
Mm-hmm! I bet that's
where Eden is, too!

00:19:43.316 --> 00:19:45.285 position:21% line:83% align:start
However,
we don't even know

00:19:45.318 --> 00:19:47.287 position:16% line:83% align:start
if the song's
about Eden's location.

00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:50.158 position:35% line:83% align:start
You know what? That's
probably reversed, too.

00:19:50.190 --> 00:19:52.627 position:30% line:83% align:start
As in, I'm not actually
looking for Eden,

00:19:52.660 --> 00:19:55.429 position:41% line:83% align:start
but that it's been
making me look for <i>it.</i>

00:19:55.462 --> 00:19:57.632 position:30% line:83% align:start
And each time I stumble
upon something,

00:19:57.665 --> 00:20:00.134 position:27% line:83% align:start
I have this feeling that
someone will let me know

00:20:00.168 --> 00:20:01.836 position:50% line:83% align:start
if I've made
the right choice.

00:20:01.869 --> 00:20:03.403 position:5% line:89% align:start
And who would that be?

00:20:03.437 --> 00:20:07.108 position:24% line:83% align:start
We'll find out. Let's go.
Let's join the others.

00:20:07.141 --> 00:20:11.179 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:20:11.211 --> 00:20:13.047 position:19% line:89% align:start
Everything is in place.

00:20:13.081 --> 00:20:15.817 position:30% line:83% align:start
All that's left
is for you to choose.

00:20:31.298 --> 00:20:34.068 position:50% line:83% align:start
"The reverse
also holds true."

00:20:34.102 --> 00:20:35.302 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's</i> what it meant.

00:20:35.335 --> 00:20:38.139 position:21% line:83% align:start
-"Virgin Virus," huh?
-No! It's "Vice Versa"!

00:20:38.172 --> 00:20:41.241 position:16% line:83% align:start
This location
isn't even that far away.

00:20:41.274 --> 00:20:44.112 position:44% line:83% align:start
It really isn't.
Yukimaru!

00:20:44.145 --> 00:20:47.148 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hm?
-How are you feeling?

00:20:47.181 --> 00:20:49.183 position:44% line:83% align:start
Everything's fine.
Shitan!

00:20:49.217 --> 00:20:50.250 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:20:50.283 --> 00:20:53.453 position:27% line:83% align:start
You gonna be okay
with this?

00:20:54.354 --> 00:20:58.226 position:7% line:83% align:start
[ Chuckles softly ]
Yes. All good.

00:20:58.258 --> 00:21:00.728 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:21:00.762 --> 00:21:03.131 position:64% line:89% align:start
Hmnh.

00:21:03.164 --> 00:21:05.666 position:47% line:77% align:start
Hm.
[ Both chuckle ]

00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.702 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:21:12.305 --> 00:21:15.475 position:30% line:83% align:start
My whole life,
things kept on happening to me.

00:21:15.510 --> 00:21:18.646 position:27% line:83% align:start
I never knew why
and didn't know what to do.

00:21:18.679 --> 00:21:22.250 position:35% line:83% align:start
But now...
I'll find those answers in Eden.

00:21:22.282 --> 00:21:25.219 position:33% line:83% align:start
That is what
I've come to believe.

00:21:25.253 --> 00:21:26.854 position:7% line:89% align:start
Because when I think about it,

00:21:26.888 --> 00:21:29.056 position:19% line:83% align:start
Eden's what brought me
to all of you.

00:21:29.090 --> 00:21:33.694 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm aware that I'd be making a
bunch of trouble for you again.

00:21:33.728 --> 00:21:37.131 position:7% line:83% align:start
But I want to travel the world
with all of you...

00:21:37.165 --> 00:21:39.834 position:7% line:89% align:start
and take this journey together!

00:21:39.867 --> 00:21:42.904 position:13% line:83% align:start
I don't know what's waiting
for us up ahead,

00:21:42.937 --> 00:21:45.940 position:10% line:83% align:start
but if you'll put your faith
in me and follow my lead,

00:21:45.973 --> 00:21:47.374 position:21% line:89% align:start
I won't let you down!

00:21:47.407 --> 00:21:50.178 position:27% line:83% align:start
Now set a course!
For Eden!

00:21:50.211 --> 00:21:52.113 position:27% line:89% align:start
We go...together!

00:21:52.146 --> 00:21:53.247 position:38% line:89% align:start
All: Aye!

00:21:53.281 --> 00:21:54.314 position:44% line:83% align:start
Enju:
Bring on the trouble!

00:21:54.347 --> 00:21:55.983 position:41% line:83% align:start
Kaede:
We eat trouble for breakfast!

00:21:56.017 --> 00:21:58.820 position:41% line:77% align:start
Karin:
Obviously I have to go 'cause
Fena's hopeless without me.

00:21:58.853 --> 00:22:01.622 position:7% line:83% align:start
Shitan: [ Sighs ] This is going
to be another rowdy trip.

00:22:01.656 --> 00:22:03.991 position:41% line:83% align:start
Makaba:
First things first! Food!

00:22:04.025 --> 00:22:06.194 position:16% line:89% align:start
